</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1671,2019]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,470]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,262,1708,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,339,1708,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[354,460,1707,1731]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[200,1365,176,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,145,1247]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Psilochlorops, head, dorsal and lateral view. 1, 7. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 2, 8. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 3, 9. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 4, 10. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 5, 11. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 6, 12. Psilochlorops flavisoma (holotype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214703/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Figs. 2, 8</figureCitation>
). Head brown dorsally, yellowish ventrally, as wide as thorax, broader than long in dorsal view, as long as high in lateral view; frontal triangle brown, margins only slightly sinuose, not reaching anterior margin of frons; occiput dark, bare; gena yellow, about 
<number box="[783,832,1779,1803]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" value="0.25">0.25</number>
eye height, postgena about half eye height; eye oval, long axis diagonal; clypeus brownish, dusted; labella brown; palpus yellow basally, brown in the apex; face with a brown stripe ¾ ateriorly. First flagellomere yellow basally, dark brown on distal half; arista dark brown; one row of interfrontals external to frontal triangle; postocellars convergent; inner and outer verticals well–developed; more than one row of setulae at lower margin of gena, no distinct vibrissa. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[922,1010,1924,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1026,1119,1923,1947]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[197,1394,607,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,574,1926]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Psilochlorops, mesonotum, dorsal view. 13. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 14. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 15. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 16. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 17. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 18. Psilochlorops flavisoma (paratype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214704/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Figs. 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1131,1160,1923,1947]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1579,1602]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,720,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,695,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 19. Habitus. 20. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 21. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214705/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">19</figureCitation>
). Scutum mostly brown, with three dark brown stripes, less than twice as long as broad, with dark pilosity; scutellum dark yellow. Pleura mostly brownish, post–pronotum yellow, with a brown mark, bristles probably broken; pleural sclerites quite homogeneously dark brown. Halter with stem brown, knob pale yellow. Legs dark yellow, hind tibia dark brown, tibial organ brownish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[407,471,187,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Wing</emphasis>
. Slightly brownish. Costal sections one to four: 
<date box="[1024,1142,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1916-01-16" valueMax="1916-01-04" valueMin="1916-01-16">
<number box="[1024,1055,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="16.0">16</number>
- 
<number box="[1063,1094,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="16.0">16</number>
- 
<number box="[1103,1120,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
- 
<number box="[1128,1138,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</date>
R 
<number box="[1169,1177,203,217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1186,1193,203,217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
and R 
<number box="[1265,1273,203,217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1282,1289,203,217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="5.0">5</number>
slightly concave; R 
<number box="[235,243,242,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[252,259,242,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[335,341,242,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[350,359,242,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
paralell; M 
<number box="[489,495,242,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[504,513,242,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
straight; r-m and dm-cu rather convergent, distant each other 
<number box="[1199,1234,226,250]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="2.5">2.5</number>
as long as dm-cu. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,265,290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[284,369,265,289]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1579,1602]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,720,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,695,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 19. Habitus. 20. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 21. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214705/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[338,369,265,289]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites and sternites brown, yellowish along distal margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1078,1209,265,290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Hypandrium wide, with broad ventral projections weakly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[721,805,301,325]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1579,1602]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,720,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,695,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 19. Habitus. 20. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 21. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214705/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[773,805,301,325]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus setose, clavate, fused to epandrium; mesolobus almost square (
<figureCitation box="[367,450,337,361]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1579,1602]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,720,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,695,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 19. Habitus. 20. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 21. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214705/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[419,450,337,361]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,470]" box="[201,420,373,398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,295,374,398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,337,409,434]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Comments.</emphasis>
The brown pleural sclerites in this species are unique in the genus, and the male terminalia also helps to clearly distinguish this species from other 
<taxonomicName box="[720,875,446,470]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Psilochlorops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[720,875,446,470]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Psilochlorops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
